@page
@model Alcohol_Label.Pages.DocumentationModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Documentation";
}

<section class="page-header">
    <h1>Project Documentation</h1>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Purpose</h2>
    <p>
        This application demonstrates an alcohol label verification workflow. It extracts label fields,
        checks required information, and presents a pass/fail review summary.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Architecture</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Razor Pages:</strong> Handles upload, review, and documentation screens.</li>
        <li><strong>Models:</strong> Represent extracted label data and verification results.</li>
        <li><strong>Services:</strong> Separate Gemini OCR extraction, expected-value comparison, and compliance validation.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Assumptions</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>The OCR service uses the Gemini API for image/PDF uploads.</li>
        <li>Pasted text and text files are still supported for easier testing.</li>
        <li>The Gemini API key is loaded from configuration and should not be committed to source control.</li>
        <li>Expected values are optional; when entered, mismatches are marked for review.</li>
        <li>The verification rules are simplified and intended for a take-home prototype.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Future Improvements</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Add a rule database for different alcohol categories and jurisdictions.</li>
        <li>Persist uploads and verification history.</li>
        <li>Add reviewer notes and manual override workflow.</li>
    </ul>
</section>
